This paper is about learning generative models using denoising density estimators (DDEs), which is a technique in unsupervised machine learning. The paper discusses the use of neural networks to represent a kernel density estimator of the data, which is a common approach in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these sub-categories are closely related to unsupervised learning and neural networks. Additionally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Sound) are also possible sub-categories, as the paper discusses the use of neural networks and provides experimental results.
